page.title: 01General (East) Headcorn Kent
page.content: A Rural Parish in the Weald of Kent, East of{Headcorn}village where, W.Kent adjoins E.Kent. Mostly agricultural; small mixed farms with dairy cattle, sheep,corn crops and hay. Nurseries grow flowers,vegatables and soft fruit for market.Lush undulating countryside fields for grazing with hedgerows be- tween, lining narrow lanes and roads. Trees are mostly deciduous; numerous ponds and small streams - some with fish; and many old farmhouses. S - W corner only built up area;modern houses,bungalows and old cottages; a Public House; a few small industries cluster round a curve of the A274 main road to Maidstone. Local inhabitants have been joined by retired people and many newcomers who commute to business in towns served by the main Ashford to London railway line immediately to the South of this block.
